problems.problem:
On $\mathbb{R} ^n$, define two operations
    \begin{align*}
        \alpha \oplus \beta & = \alpha - \beta, \\
        c \odot \alpha & = - c \alpha.
    \end{align*}
    The operations on the right are the usual ones. Which of the axioms for a vector space are satisfied by $\left( \mathbb{R} ^n, \oplus, \odot \right) $?

Let $V$ be the set of pairs $(x, y)$ of real numbers and let $\mathbb{F} $ be the field of real numbers. Define 
     \begin{align*}
        (x,y) + (x_1, y_1) & = (x + x_1, 0) \\
        c (x,y) & = (c x, 0).
     \end{align*}
     Is $V$, with these operations, a vector space?
